        <div n="952B14W2" type="poem"><head type="note" n="1" xml:id="spp-952B14W2-headnote-1"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-952B14W2-headnote-1-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-952B14W2-headnote-1-line-group-1-line-1">ONIONS.</l></lg></head><head type="note" n="2" xml:id="spp-952B14W2-headnote-2"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-952B14W2-headnote-2-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-952B14W2-headnote-2-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head><head type="note" n="3" xml:id="spp-952B14W2-headnote-3"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-952B14W2-headnote-3-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-952B14W2-headnote-3-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head>
      <lg n="1" type="stanza"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-952B14W2-line-1">C<hi rend="SMALL-CAPS">OME</hi>, follow me by the smell,Here are delicate onions to sell;I promise to use you well.They make the blood warmer,You'll feed like a farmer;</l><l n="2" xml:id="spp-952B14W2-line-2"> For this is every cook's opinion,</l><l n="3" xml:id="spp-952B14W2-line-3"> No savoury dish without an onion;</l><l n="4" xml:id="spp-952B14W2-line-4"> But, lest your kissing should be spoil'd,</l><l n="5" xml:id="spp-952B14W2-line-5"> Your onions must be thoroughly boil'd:Or else you may spareYour mistress a share,</l><l n="6" xml:id="spp-952B14W2-line-6"> The secret will never be known:She cannot discoverThe breath of her lover,</l><l n="7" xml:id="spp-952B14W2-line-7"> But think it as sweet as her own.952B14W2   </l></lg></div>
      </div>
